[div class=p 
	[em 
		"Formation Z
	]em
	" is a sideway auto-scrolling shooting game in which the player controls a robot character that can transform into a jet to "DESTROY ALIENS WEAPON".
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"The scrolling speed of the screen can be changed according to the state of the character, and bosses may only appear when certain conditions are met, 
	$LF
	"which allows the length of the gameplay to vary a lot.
	$LF
	"The jet form advances much faster than the robot form, however the speed varies depending on the height of the flight.
	$LF
	"Fuel is usually lacked in casaul gameplay and requires replenishing, but not in this run.
	$LF
	"Actually, no fuel replenishment is needed even if the player advanced at maximum speed all the time without abusing deaths, thanks to a glitch.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"Originally, this run was deathless (see below) and intended for April Fools' Gruefood 2014 as a satire on the bias against usage of deaths to save time in Arcade TASes.
	$LF
	"However TASVideos.org then changed the movie rules to allow pure speed-oriented runs for the Vault Tier, invalidating that purpose.
	$LF
	"The author then decided to abuse deaths in the run, which merely helps to skip a game event.
	$LF
	"This run was soon completed with 6725 input frames.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	[em 
		"But in the end, this run has turned out to be suited for a different irony. Hurrah!
	]em
	$LF
]div
